        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 8:23PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 823 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Knowles, or 14 miles southwest of Englewood, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gate and Knowles.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
